"{\"uid\": \"geo.tv-latest-557246-google-pulls-ai-ad-that-irked-some-olympics-viewers\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"August 03, 2024  SAN FRANCISCO: Google confirmed Friday that it had pulled an ad for its Gemini artificial intelligence after it landed flat with some Olympics viewers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 38, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9989410092755515, \"rank\": 0.0010598513543241983, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.6599097711865791, \"rank\": 0.5153586802764987, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Dear Sydney\\\" ad, intended to tout capabilities of Gemini AI, featured a dad warmly describing how the tool wrote his daughter a fan letter from her to US hurdler Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.6599097711865791, \"rank\": 0.5153586802764987, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}, {\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.983222735502912, \"rank\": 0.0160546676457014, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 337, \"end\": 343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999630035265371, \"rank\": 2.7229455855333868e-05, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, some viewers bashed the ad as promoting the notion that parents should coax their children to rely on AI rather than learn to express themselves.\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 476, \"end\": 478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While the ad tested well before airing, given the feedback, we have decided to phase the ad out of our Olympics rotation,\\\" a Google spokesperson told AFP.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9994914985603471, \"rank\": 0.0005036752999092889, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media posts fired off on an array of platforms questioned whether the ad signaled a dystopian future in which human creativity atrophies due to AI.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Syracuse University media professor Shelly Palmer said the commercial suggested that a poorly worded prompt to a generative AI tool can express a person\\u00b4s feeling better than they could themselves.\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.9999969158356902, \"rank\": 1.8275902740572454e-06, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}, {\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero sucks,\\\" author Linda Holmes wrote in a post on BlueSky.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999999999938609, \"rank\": 6.027643145579531e-12, \"text\": \"Linda Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"score\": 0.934115051658946, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BlueSky\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Who wants an AI-written fan letter?\\\"\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tech evangelists have touted the promised benefits of AI, but teachers, musicians, artists and others have accused its creators of training advanced computers to replace them.\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999985568341754, \"rank\": 1.4429864192089818e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Early this year, Apple had an ad stumble of its own with a commercial showing musical instruments, paint cans and other creative gear crushed and replaced by an iPad to the tune of a song titled \\\"All I Ever Need Is You.\\\"\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1413, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.999999999960437, \"rank\": 3.901503258049474e-11, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"score\": 0.9969122028801608, \"rank\": 0.003091571245086245, \"text\": \"iPad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Geo Television Network.\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geo_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Geo Television Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geo_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geo_TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"|Contact Us|Authors|Privacy Policy\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": []}]}"